WEBVTT

00:32.323 --> 00:33.533
♪ <i>Louie, Louie ♪</i>

00:35.035 --> 00:36.119
[vocalizing]

00:40.373 --> 00:42.959
<i>♪ Aye-yi-yi-yi ♪</i>

00:43.043 --> 00:45.045
♪ <i>Louie, Louie… ♪</i>

00:45.795 --> 00:47.630
[vocalizing]

00:49.299 --> 00:51.718
[Phoebe] All you have to do
is make the exchange.

00:51.801 --> 00:54.012
-[Dave] Unique New York.
-What if he figures it out?

00:54.095 --> 00:55.597
We'll protect you.

00:55.680 --> 00:58.391
Red leather, yellow leather.
Red leather, yellow leather.

00:58.475 --> 01:00.560
His gun's the size of my arm.

01:00.643 --> 01:01.936
We're Secret Service.

01:02.645 --> 01:05.356
-So?
-Ever seen <i>In the Line of Fire?</i>

01:06.024 --> 01:07.358
You'll take a bullet for me?

01:08.359 --> 01:09.194
He will.

01:09.277 --> 01:11.446
Betty Botter
bought a bit of bitter butter.

01:11.529 --> 01:14.240
But the bit of butter
was too bitter for the batter.

01:20.622 --> 01:23.041
[Beth]<i> What if he goes crazy</i>
<i>and kidnaps me?</i>

01:23.124 --> 01:26.711
Already tagged his car.
You just do what you've always done.

01:26.795 --> 01:27.962
[microphone feedback]

01:29.422 --> 01:32.675
-It's not gonna do that, is it?
-[sighs] Let's hope not.

01:35.345 --> 01:37.305
<i>♪ Aye-yi-yi-yi ♪</i>

01:58.201 --> 01:59.994
-He knows.
-He doesn't.

02:00.078 --> 02:01.287
Yeah, he does.

02:01.371 --> 02:02.205
[Dave] He might.

02:03.665 --> 02:05.875
-Seriously?
-Tracker just went dead.

02:07.752 --> 02:09.546
I want a cop outside my house.

02:09.629 --> 02:10.880
That'll just draw attention.

02:10.964 --> 02:12.715
So will my dead body in the Detroit River.

02:12.799 --> 02:15.301
-Let's not lose our heads.
-I want my husband out.

02:15.385 --> 02:18.638
-Not till we know where the money goes.
-I did everything you said.

02:18.721 --> 02:20.181
Except the only part that matters.

02:20.265 --> 02:21.391
That's not on me.

02:21.975 --> 02:22.892
Kinda is.

02:29.190 --> 02:30.859
Trackers sometimes glitch.

02:42.954 --> 02:45.832
-[door opens]
-[Nancy] Wait. What is a pet emergency?

02:45.915 --> 02:48.710
Because this is an actual emergency.

02:48.793 --> 02:49.711
Nanny flaked.

02:49.794 --> 02:51.212
-Where's Dad?
-[Ben] Chicago.

02:51.296 --> 02:53.047
-[Dakota coos]
-Some zit cream convention.

02:53.131 --> 02:56.759
Yes! Samples.
Why do none of these friggin' things work?

02:58.344 --> 03:01.556
[Nancy] Well, how does tomorrow
help me when the meeting is today?

03:01.639 --> 03:02.640
Okay. Okay, okay.

03:02.724 --> 03:07.312
Um, why don't you just, uh,
let me know about Gizmo's MRI, okay?

03:07.395 --> 03:09.105
-[Dakota crying]
-Bye.

03:09.188 --> 03:11.274
Why don't you
get somebody to cover for you?

03:11.357 --> 03:14.360
Because it's not like
your mini-mart. I own the company.

03:14.444 --> 03:15.862
So, reschedule the meeting.

03:15.945 --> 03:18.489
It's a whole thing with the bank.

03:18.573 --> 03:19.866
I could take him.

03:22.994 --> 03:23.912
Really?

03:23.995 --> 03:25.413
You have school.

03:25.496 --> 03:26.706
Well, can't he skip?

03:27.749 --> 03:28.917
It's one day.

03:29.000 --> 03:30.543
You always did, right?

03:31.878 --> 03:33.379
Not happening, my friend.

03:34.422 --> 03:36.341
Mom, what is she supposed to do?

03:36.424 --> 03:38.593
Uh, I don't know.
Find literally anyone else.

03:38.676 --> 03:40.637
-There's no one else.
-Well…

03:40.720 --> 03:41.721
[sighs]

03:42.347 --> 03:45.016
What about the retired guy
who sleeps on his front porch?

03:45.099 --> 03:46.726
He's not allowed around kids.

03:47.602 --> 03:49.020
Your pool guy's like family.

03:49.103 --> 03:51.231
He smokes weed all day in his truck.

03:51.314 --> 03:53.900
Come on. Alex will bring me my homework.

03:55.151 --> 03:56.152
[smacks lips]

03:56.736 --> 03:57.987
I'll do it.

04:00.949 --> 04:02.951
But Alex will be at school.

04:03.826 --> 04:04.702
No, no, I…

04:05.495 --> 04:07.497
I mean, I will watch Dakota.

04:09.832 --> 04:10.833
[Dakota crying]

04:14.837 --> 04:15.755
Sorry.

04:16.965 --> 04:18.174
Why can't I do it?

04:19.008 --> 04:21.386
You can't even take care of the turtle.

04:21.469 --> 04:24.222
How was I supposed to know
that green stuff was mold?

04:24.305 --> 04:27.100
-You can't even change a lightbulb.
-Those are all duds.

04:31.980 --> 04:34.065
[scoffs] Obviously, I…

04:34.899 --> 04:37.443
tried that. Look, I raised you.

04:38.027 --> 04:38.987
Barely.

04:39.070 --> 04:40.238
<i>Excusez-moi?</i>

04:41.364 --> 04:42.865
Auntie Beth took me every day.

04:42.949 --> 04:44.993
Because I was finishing eleventh grade.

04:45.910 --> 04:47.662
-It's fine. I'll figure it out.
-[tutting]

04:48.663 --> 04:49.622
Drop the kid.

04:50.957 --> 04:52.292
It's very sweet of you to offer.

04:52.375 --> 04:54.794
Do you remember
when they found that toddler

04:54.877 --> 04:56.713
wandering alone in the woods?

04:56.796 --> 04:59.173
He made it for three days on his own.

05:02.510 --> 05:03.845
I'm only one day.

05:07.724 --> 05:09.058
If anything happens…

05:09.142 --> 05:11.227
Nothing's gonna happen. [scoffs]

05:11.978 --> 05:14.564
-Something's gonna happen.
-Go. Come on. Put it there.

05:15.940 --> 05:16.858
-Okay.
-Yeah.

05:16.941 --> 05:19.652
All right.
The wipes are under the diapers.

05:19.736 --> 05:20.611
Check.

05:20.695 --> 05:23.239
-Butt rash stuff is in the side pocket.
-Check.

05:23.323 --> 05:25.450
The binkie is in a Ziploc with the snacks.

05:25.533 --> 05:26.993
Checkity, check, check.

05:27.994 --> 05:32.373
And Mommy will always,
always love you so, so much.

05:32.457 --> 05:35.293
I think that's enough. Go, go. Go.

05:36.919 --> 05:38.838
-Go!
-Okay.

05:40.048 --> 05:41.049
[door closes]

05:41.132 --> 05:42.341
[Dakota gurgling]

05:46.304 --> 05:47.680
Guess I got school.

05:52.685 --> 05:53.686
[Dakota crying]

05:56.856 --> 05:57.857
[phone vibrating]

05:59.400 --> 06:00.401
Hey, baby.

06:00.985 --> 06:02.487
I forgot the sauce.

06:02.570 --> 06:04.072
What are you talking about?

06:04.155 --> 06:06.157
<i>The chimichurri for your lunch.</i>

06:06.240 --> 06:07.533
Ooh. Uh, doesn't need it.

06:07.617 --> 06:09.494
-Meatloaf and no chimichurri?
-[laughs]

06:09.577 --> 06:10.620
Don't worry about it.

06:10.703 --> 06:12.371
<i>-I'll just drop it off.</i>
-Nah.

06:12.455 --> 06:13.956
I'm in the neighborhood.

06:14.040 --> 06:17.585
No, no, no. It's crazy here.
You know how it is on Wing Wednesday.

06:17.668 --> 06:20.630
I'm not getting on the pole, Stan.
I'll put it in the fridge.

06:20.713 --> 06:22.381
-I already ate it.
<i>-You did?</i>

06:23.091 --> 06:25.176
Well, I'm eating now.

06:26.886 --> 06:28.679
-Not too dry?
<i>-Mmm-mmm.</i>

06:28.763 --> 06:31.599
Mmm-mmm.
It's just as good sans sauce. Mmm.

06:31.682 --> 06:33.059
[pretend munching]

06:34.435 --> 06:36.395
I find that hard to believe.

06:36.479 --> 06:37.897
[muffled music playing]

06:41.776 --> 06:43.402
You want me to lie to you?

06:43.486 --> 06:46.030
<i>Just want to make sure</i>
<i>you're taken care of.</i>

06:46.114 --> 06:47.156
Always, baby.

06:48.574 --> 06:50.201
<i>-Cool.</i>
-Cool.

06:51.035 --> 06:52.161
Later, Hill.

06:53.246 --> 06:54.372
Later, Hill.

07:08.094 --> 07:10.513
I'd take that sauce if you're offering.

07:26.863 --> 07:28.197
[Beth grunting softly]

07:46.007 --> 07:47.717
Dean hides junk food.

07:52.305 --> 07:53.556
Where were you last night?

08:06.319 --> 08:07.445
What are you doing?

09:33.531 --> 09:34.991
Better watch your back.

09:36.909 --> 09:37.910
[door opens]

09:40.121 --> 09:41.122
[door closes]

09:47.295 --> 09:48.504
[Beth] Maybe he doesn't know.

09:49.922 --> 09:52.508
At a minimum, he suspects.

09:53.801 --> 09:55.219
I read about this lady

09:55.303 --> 09:58.055
who turned on her drug dealer in Florida.

09:58.139 --> 09:59.265
Stop reading those.

09:59.348 --> 10:00.474
Wired up.

10:00.558 --> 10:03.060
Surveillance helicopter tracked her.

10:03.144 --> 10:05.855
-The whole shebang.
-That doesn't mean it's gonna be us.

10:05.938 --> 10:08.566
They found her stuffed in a suitcase.

10:08.649 --> 10:09.734
I can't. [sighs]

10:11.485 --> 10:14.238
She was shot with the gun

10:14.322 --> 10:16.991
that the cops sent her to buy.

10:17.074 --> 10:18.200
I cannot.

10:19.577 --> 10:20.911
At the airport.

10:23.706 --> 10:24.707
How is this helping?

10:24.790 --> 10:26.584
She was his carry-on.

10:28.169 --> 10:30.004
-[door opens]
-[Dakota crying]

10:30.087 --> 10:33.299
It's like I give him the bah-bah
because he acts like he wants it.

10:33.382 --> 10:34.550
But then he doesn't want it.

10:34.634 --> 10:37.845
And then, when I take it away,
he wants it again. Like, what… [scoffs]

10:38.471 --> 10:40.431
-Why'd you bring him here?
-[groans]

10:41.515 --> 10:42.516
[sighs]

10:43.351 --> 10:45.811
-[Dakota continues crying]
-I've tried everything.

10:46.312 --> 10:47.480
Excuse me.

10:47.563 --> 10:49.315
I mean, there's heavy machinery.

10:49.398 --> 10:52.276
I've gone all Harvey Karp
on his ass at this point.

10:52.360 --> 10:54.945
With the shushing,
and the swaddling and the shaking--

10:55.029 --> 10:56.322
Shaking's not one of them.

10:56.405 --> 10:57.782
This is exactly why I need you.

10:59.241 --> 11:00.618
Oh. Oh, now you want it.

11:00.701 --> 11:02.161
We have bigger problems here.

11:02.244 --> 11:03.954
-Will you just give it to him?
-No way.

11:04.038 --> 11:07.458
This is a sick, twisted little game
he's playing. I won't give in.

11:08.042 --> 11:09.877
-Give me that.
-Well…

11:10.711 --> 11:11.796
[Dakota stops crying]

11:14.340 --> 11:15.800
What's up your butt?

11:17.385 --> 11:18.969
I'll tell you what isn't.

11:20.596 --> 11:21.597
Oh.

11:22.348 --> 11:23.224
Huh.

11:23.808 --> 11:24.975
What?

11:25.059 --> 11:27.228
I don't know. Just not what I imagined.

11:28.229 --> 11:29.688
What did you imagine?

11:29.772 --> 11:32.191
You know, something sleeker.

11:32.274 --> 11:35.694
This is kind of giving me,
like, '90s pager vibes.

11:36.904 --> 11:39.698
-She's not wrong.
-I mean, not something to track a car.

11:39.782 --> 11:41.951
-[Dakota crying]
-Oh, God.

11:42.034 --> 11:44.120
-[door opens]
-[Mick] Kid's hungry.

11:44.203 --> 11:45.496
[Dakota continues crying]

11:49.166 --> 11:50.042
[Mick] Got a bottle?

11:51.085 --> 11:53.045
[Annie] Uh… I… It's…

11:54.380 --> 11:55.756
[Mick] Seconds count.

11:56.549 --> 11:57.633
[shushing]

11:57.716 --> 11:58.926
Got a lovey?

11:59.009 --> 12:00.970
Okay, what is… What's a…

12:01.053 --> 12:02.930
-Oh, the…
-[Mick shushing]

12:04.682 --> 12:06.392
I'm not gonna need those.

12:09.311 --> 12:10.813
He doesn't want the drop?

12:11.439 --> 12:12.815
It's not drop day.

12:15.067 --> 12:16.235
What day is it?

12:17.653 --> 12:19.029
Just go get in the car.

12:21.866 --> 12:23.033
Uh, she…

12:23.117 --> 12:24.160
She can't.

12:24.994 --> 12:25.911
I can't.

12:27.204 --> 12:28.330
Why's that?

12:31.167 --> 12:32.376
The baby.

12:33.836 --> 12:34.962
What about it?

12:35.671 --> 12:37.548
I can't be left alone with him.

12:39.675 --> 12:42.344
-[Mick] And what about you?
-My kids are grown.

12:42.428 --> 12:43.429
[Dakota cooing]

12:45.222 --> 12:46.891
[Mick] Then this won't be fun.

12:48.934 --> 12:51.061
"Seafare Pool and Patio."

12:51.437 --> 12:53.397
Mmm. Sounds nice.

12:53.481 --> 12:54.899
Back on the horse.

12:54.982 --> 12:57.568
Do what you love,
you don't work a day in your life.

12:57.651 --> 13:00.362
[scoffs] Too bad my boss
is such a D-I-C-K.

13:00.446 --> 13:02.281
You can swear in here.

13:02.364 --> 13:04.158
[sighs] She's the worst.

13:04.241 --> 13:05.868
[laughs] Can't be worse than Gayle.

13:09.747 --> 13:10.998
Are you kidding me?

13:11.081 --> 13:12.541
No, who else would hire me?

13:13.209 --> 13:14.043
[scoffs]

13:14.543 --> 13:16.504
Bet she loves that I'm in here.

13:18.130 --> 13:19.215
Mmm…

13:21.008 --> 13:22.092
[sighs]

13:22.176 --> 13:24.220
Well, made any friends?

13:25.179 --> 13:26.514
It's not a frat.

13:27.515 --> 13:29.266
-Least you get to work out.
-Mmm.

13:30.267 --> 13:33.312
You have to be
in the Blood Lords to use the equipment.

13:34.813 --> 13:37.525
Well, what about classes?
You know, like art?

13:37.608 --> 13:39.443
You know, pass the time.

13:39.527 --> 13:41.403
Can't use paintbrushes anymore.

13:42.112 --> 13:42.988
Why?

13:43.072 --> 13:46.700
This lifer? He plucked
a guard's eyeball out with one.

13:47.451 --> 13:48.285
Ugh.

13:48.786 --> 13:50.079
That's raw, dawg.

13:53.541 --> 13:55.459
I've got to get out of here, man.

13:57.753 --> 14:00.047
-How's Beth doing with the bail?
-[chuckles]

14:00.130 --> 14:03.008
I think she wants me in here. King me.

14:03.634 --> 14:05.386
Why would she want that?

14:05.970 --> 14:08.639
So she can hump
the tats off her boyfriend. [scoffs]

14:10.140 --> 14:11.350
Mmm.

14:18.107 --> 14:19.692
I'm gonna get you out.

14:20.401 --> 14:22.695
How are you gonna score a hundred grand?

14:23.988 --> 14:25.531
Let me worry about that.

14:25.614 --> 14:27.032
You live in a basement.

14:27.116 --> 14:28.200
You're my best friend.

14:28.284 --> 14:29.285
With a roommate.

14:31.287 --> 14:32.246
Your move.

14:34.874 --> 14:36.333
Are you letting me win?

14:45.384 --> 14:47.136
Don't get too comfy in here.

14:52.766 --> 14:53.851
[door buzzes]

14:58.480 --> 15:00.524
Oh, no, no, no. I'm good, man.

15:00.608 --> 15:02.067
Come on, join me.

15:02.860 --> 15:04.945
Ah, you know, it's the middle of the day.

15:05.029 --> 15:07.948
That's why I don't wear a watch. Come on.

15:08.032 --> 15:09.283
[chuckles]

15:10.326 --> 15:11.327
[sighs]

15:19.585 --> 15:20.502
Yeah.

15:21.629 --> 15:23.172
[breathes deeply]

15:27.134 --> 15:28.969
You're a good guy, Stan.

15:32.222 --> 15:33.474
Uh, thanks.

15:35.142 --> 15:36.268
You're funny.

15:37.311 --> 15:39.188
You know how to talk to people.

15:42.566 --> 15:44.443
Not too bad on the eyes, either.

15:46.236 --> 15:47.863
-What's that?
-You work out?

15:49.365 --> 15:52.284
Uh, I hit the gym when I can.

15:52.368 --> 15:55.788
Bet those girls at the club
can't keep their hands off you, huh?

15:55.871 --> 15:57.081
Stanimal, huh?

15:58.040 --> 16:00.668
Hey, man, there's no touching
in the champagne room.

16:00.751 --> 16:02.419
Don't got to worry about me.

16:08.217 --> 16:10.219
Who do I got to worry about, Gene?

16:10.302 --> 16:12.846
Someone I want to be in business with.

16:16.892 --> 16:17.810
Why me?

16:19.103 --> 16:20.646
I can't seem to close her.

16:22.690 --> 16:24.316
-I have a wife.
-Oh.

16:24.400 --> 16:26.402
Oh, the bitch who stole my money.

16:26.944 --> 16:27.778
Come on now.

16:27.861 --> 16:31.073
I'd be happy to
put her to work if you're not up to it.

16:33.534 --> 16:34.535
[sighs]

16:38.831 --> 16:41.000
She's in room 216.

16:41.792 --> 16:42.835
What's the deal?

16:48.424 --> 16:49.425
[Dakota crying]

16:55.097 --> 16:57.099
It's easier if you put it on the side.

16:58.058 --> 16:59.435
What are you on, crack?

17:01.478 --> 17:02.938
She is not.

17:03.022 --> 17:05.649
Middle's the safest spot in the vehicle.

17:06.400 --> 17:07.526
Whatever works.

17:11.113 --> 17:12.239
Let's roll.

17:14.700 --> 17:17.995
Y'all realize we're using
a baby as a human shield.

17:19.288 --> 17:20.748
[Dakota continues crying]

17:25.169 --> 17:26.670
[Dakota crying]

17:45.606 --> 17:46.982
You're gonna need this.

17:48.150 --> 17:49.610
And this.

17:52.571 --> 17:53.947
Why can't he do it?

17:54.490 --> 17:55.908
Boss is laying low.

17:56.575 --> 17:57.993
And why can't you do it?

17:59.203 --> 18:00.329
You're the banker.

18:02.498 --> 18:03.749
-[Ruby sighs]
-[door closes]

18:08.587 --> 18:10.047
Maybe it'll be okay.

18:10.714 --> 18:11.757
How so?

18:15.761 --> 18:17.429
You can't kill the banker.

18:18.639 --> 18:19.807
Unless…

18:21.183 --> 18:24.311
whoever's waiting
behind that door is gonna take you out.

18:25.979 --> 18:28.357
Not every thought
in that head has to come out.

18:28.440 --> 18:31.318
Ooh. Plus, he took the tracker
so they have no idea where we are.

18:31.401 --> 18:32.444
There's another one.

19:02.349 --> 19:04.560
[French pop-rock song playing]

19:16.572 --> 19:17.573
Hello?

19:31.753 --> 19:32.629
Hello?

20:10.918 --> 20:12.085
Is anybody here?

20:25.474 --> 20:26.683
Nobody move!

20:28.268 --> 20:30.270
Give me the '52 Mantle rookie.

20:37.611 --> 20:38.612
[door opens]

20:45.494 --> 20:46.703
Can I help you?

20:47.537 --> 20:48.455
Uh…

20:51.583 --> 20:52.793
I'm the banker?

20:53.794 --> 20:56.088
[video game on cell phone chiming]

21:00.467 --> 21:01.468
[cell phone chimes]

21:02.803 --> 21:04.554
-Is she alive?
-[sighs] No.

21:05.430 --> 21:06.598
-What?
-No.

21:06.682 --> 21:07.975
It's Nancy.

21:08.058 --> 21:10.018
She wants proof of life.

21:10.811 --> 21:12.396
Oi. Okay.

21:14.648 --> 21:16.483
-[Dakota coos]
-[camera shutter clicks]

21:17.276 --> 21:18.819
[typing]

21:18.902 --> 21:20.779
Could've used one of those from Stan.

21:22.155 --> 21:23.365
Why, where is he at?

21:24.283 --> 21:25.993
Not anywhere he says he is.

21:26.576 --> 21:27.953
I thought he, like, lived at work.

21:28.578 --> 21:29.871
That's what he says.

21:30.747 --> 21:31.999
Where's the man work?

21:34.167 --> 21:35.752
Um, Sweet P's.

21:37.379 --> 21:39.798
[laughs] Place with the shaved ham?

21:39.881 --> 21:41.133
Oh, whoa.

21:41.216 --> 21:42.676
We prefer gentlemen's club.

21:42.759 --> 21:43.635
Why?

21:45.012 --> 21:46.972
I mean, you gonna say it or am I?

21:48.015 --> 21:49.182
Come on.

21:52.102 --> 21:53.103
Say what?

21:53.186 --> 21:54.730
He's a bouncer.

21:56.106 --> 21:59.318
And I bet those chicks
know how to show their appreciation.

21:59.401 --> 22:01.862
Okay, you know what?
This is a family matter, so…

22:01.945 --> 22:03.739
Um, you don't know my husband.

22:04.281 --> 22:08.160
You're right. Man's got
lady gardens in his face all day.

22:09.077 --> 22:10.871
Bet he can't wait to get home.

22:12.622 --> 22:14.166
No, no, no, no, no, no.

22:14.249 --> 22:16.001
He is always tired.

22:16.084 --> 22:17.878
Because he's always working.

22:17.961 --> 22:19.713
-In lady gardens.
-[smacks lips]

22:37.773 --> 22:38.815
I'm the banker.

22:44.196 --> 22:45.822
["Mommy Can't Sleep" playing]

22:50.327 --> 22:51.203
Excuse me.

22:51.870 --> 22:53.288
Yeah, give me a minute.

22:56.208 --> 22:57.209
I'm the banker.

23:01.630 --> 23:02.714
I'll be right back.

23:05.634 --> 23:07.177
<i>♪ I don't wanna be here ♪</i>

23:07.260 --> 23:09.012
<i>♪ I don't wanna be here ♪</i>

23:09.096 --> 23:10.847
<i>♪ I don't wanna be here… ♪</i>

23:11.348 --> 23:12.474
I'm the banker.

23:12.557 --> 23:14.351
<i>♪ Why'd you bring me here? ♪</i>

23:14.434 --> 23:16.186
<i>♪ Giving me bad dreams ♪</i>

23:16.269 --> 23:18.980
<i>♪ Can't scream, bad dream ♪</i>

23:19.856 --> 23:21.858
<i>♪ How did I wake up surrounded by walls? ♪</i>

23:21.942 --> 23:23.610
<i>♪ How did I break all my bones? ♪</i>

23:23.693 --> 23:25.362
<i>♪ Keep banging the concrete</i>
<i>To blow up… ♪</i>

23:25.445 --> 23:26.530
I'm the banker.

23:27.239 --> 23:28.406
<i>♪ I'm covered in plastic… ♪</i>

23:28.490 --> 23:29.449
I'm the banker.

23:31.201 --> 23:32.285
Heard of me?

23:32.869 --> 23:34.955
Yeah, the banker.

23:38.917 --> 23:42.295
<i>♪ Mommy, wake up, I can't sleep ♪</i>

23:42.379 --> 23:46.091
♪ <i>I need some comfort from my dreams ♪</i>

23:46.174 --> 23:51.346
<i>♪ I swear I saw you dancing</i>
<i>With some specters… ♪</i>

23:51.429 --> 23:52.806
I'm the banker, bitch.

23:55.183 --> 23:57.060
-[song stops]
-What did you just call me?

23:58.478 --> 23:59.604
[chuckling] I'm sorry.

24:00.230 --> 24:01.231
I'm the banker.

24:03.358 --> 24:04.192
The what?

24:06.653 --> 24:07.904
Who's the owner here?

24:10.574 --> 24:11.616
My mom.

24:11.700 --> 24:13.118
Is she available?

24:14.744 --> 24:15.579
She's, uh…

24:16.746 --> 24:17.747
She's sick.

24:22.627 --> 24:26.131
Well, did she happen
to leave any cash around?

24:28.383 --> 24:29.342
Let me see here.

24:31.970 --> 24:34.514
I got gold bars. Bunch of diamonds.

24:35.056 --> 24:35.974
Nope.

24:36.808 --> 24:37.893
No cash.

24:39.436 --> 24:40.270
Okay.

24:41.146 --> 24:44.399
Your mother pays my employer monthly.

24:45.734 --> 24:46.693
For what?

24:47.277 --> 24:50.572
Well, I guess
you could say for protection.

24:52.073 --> 24:53.200
From who?

24:56.286 --> 24:57.370
From him.

25:00.582 --> 25:01.583
Get out of here.

25:03.710 --> 25:05.670
I'm sorry if this is a hard time.

25:05.754 --> 25:07.380
What do you want me to do?

25:08.715 --> 25:10.217
Maybe shoot her a quick call?

25:10.842 --> 25:14.888
Sure. Yeah, I'll just have the nurse
hold up the phone to her dialysis machine

25:14.971 --> 25:16.014
and you can shake it down.

25:16.097 --> 25:18.725
-Okay, I feel terrible--
-It'll magically turn into an ATM.

25:18.808 --> 25:20.810
Is there anyone else here I could talk to?

25:23.897 --> 25:25.273
What is wrong with you?

25:29.778 --> 25:31.529
I just need my money.

25:35.742 --> 25:36.701
Or what?

25:44.584 --> 25:46.086
[slurping]

25:49.297 --> 25:50.548
He text you back yet?

25:53.969 --> 25:54.970
Mmm.

25:56.763 --> 25:59.057
You know, the nipples,

25:59.140 --> 26:00.684
the G-strings…

26:00.767 --> 26:02.143
It's just what he does.

26:02.227 --> 26:03.520
It's not who he is.

26:08.275 --> 26:09.526
Are you gonna finish that?

26:13.822 --> 26:17.409
Oh, my God. Will you turn
the heat down? It's like Arizona in here.

26:18.660 --> 26:21.037
Little guy sleeps better when it's warm.

26:25.208 --> 26:26.584
He hasn't woken up yet.

26:28.086 --> 26:29.629
-[cell phone ringing]
-Oh.

26:29.713 --> 26:31.214
No! My God!

26:32.424 --> 26:34.843
-Just get it already.
-She's trying to FaceTime.

26:34.926 --> 26:35.927
-I'll get it.
-[Annie] Oh.

26:36.011 --> 26:39.681
Yeah, sure. Because the complete stranger
with the… This whole message

26:39.764 --> 26:41.516
is really gonna calm her down.

26:42.017 --> 26:44.227
-[sighs]
-[cell phone chimes]

26:44.311 --> 26:46.688
Oh, Jesus. She finished early.

26:47.897 --> 26:48.732
We…

26:55.238 --> 26:56.197
You got it?

26:56.281 --> 26:57.574
Yep. All there.

27:02.871 --> 27:05.290
-You sure?
-Positive.

27:06.333 --> 27:08.710
Because if not, you'll have a situation.

27:11.421 --> 27:12.881
Do you want to count it?

27:12.964 --> 27:14.466
[chuckles] It won't be on me.

27:14.549 --> 27:15.633
Let me guess.

27:16.259 --> 27:17.385
He trusts you.

27:21.514 --> 27:24.267
I hate to make this about me, but, uh…

27:24.851 --> 27:27.270
any chance we could
get this show on the road?

27:27.354 --> 27:28.813
[car engine starts]

27:28.897 --> 27:30.398
[upbeat pop-rock song playing]

27:31.316 --> 27:35.278
<i>♪ Do you remember</i>
<i>When you were quite small ♪</i>

27:35.362 --> 27:38.823
<i>♪ Crew cut and pigtails</i>
<i>School in the fall ♪</i>

27:38.907 --> 27:41.493
<i>♪ Autumn leaves brightened the earth ♪</i>

27:42.452 --> 27:45.288
<i>♪ A new season was giving birth ♪</i>

27:46.164 --> 27:49.542
<i>♪ To feeling that warms the soul ♪</i>

27:49.626 --> 27:52.128
<i>♪ Mother rescue for the fold ♪</i>

27:52.212 --> 27:55.423
<i>♪ Feel good, feel good, feel fine ♪</i>

27:56.257 --> 28:00.053
<i>♪ Oh, such a lovely day ♪</i>

28:00.136 --> 28:02.806
♪ <i>Feel good, feel good, feel fine ♪</i>

28:04.182 --> 28:05.683
<i>♪ Oh ♪</i>

28:05.767 --> 28:09.312
<i>♪ Years gone by, can you remember? ♪</i>

28:09.396 --> 28:12.148
<i>♪ So, pull the Christmas things</i>
<i>A warm December ♪</i>

28:12.232 --> 28:15.693
<i>♪ Think of the many years gone by ♪</i>

28:15.777 --> 28:18.822
<i>♪ Turn the page and give it a try ♪</i>

28:18.905 --> 28:22.117
<i>♪ Feel good, feel good, feel fine ♪</i>

28:22.909 --> 28:24.786
<i>♪ Oh ♪</i>

28:24.869 --> 28:30.917
<i>♪ Such a lovely daze ♪</i>

28:41.219 --> 28:46.015
<i>♪ Fantasy is sometimes real ♪</i>

28:46.933 --> 28:50.687
<i>♪ Can you understand? ♪</i>

28:52.605 --> 28:56.985
<i>♪ Life is hard</i>
<i>Have you felt what I feel? ♪</i>

28:57.068 --> 28:58.653
<i>♪ Ooh ♪</i>

28:58.737 --> 29:01.865
<i>♪ Someone takes your hand ♪</i>

29:01.948 --> 29:02.824
[girl] Mommy.

29:03.825 --> 29:05.744
Can I play a game on your phone?

29:06.536 --> 29:07.412
Yeah.

29:11.249 --> 29:12.709
Just be careful with it.

29:23.470 --> 29:24.345
Y'all open?

29:26.264 --> 29:27.432
I told you to get out.

29:27.515 --> 29:29.601
What about with one of these in your face?

29:35.732 --> 29:37.358
Just your basic Glock, right?

29:38.067 --> 29:40.320
Front and rear sights. Polymer grip.

29:40.945 --> 29:41.863
Extractor.

29:42.530 --> 29:44.908
Slide. Slide release.

29:46.493 --> 29:47.744
Blah, blah, blah.

29:50.955 --> 29:53.416
-What am I supposed to do with it?
-Pick it up.

29:54.542 --> 29:55.835
No. I don't want it.

29:55.919 --> 29:59.255
And my daughter doesn't wanna wear
a helmet when she rides her scooter.

29:59.339 --> 30:00.298
But you know what?

30:01.132 --> 30:02.675
Bad things happen.

30:04.010 --> 30:05.595
I'm sure your mom would agree.

30:08.306 --> 30:10.058
I'm gonna call the cops.

30:12.352 --> 30:13.269
Go ahead.

30:14.521 --> 30:16.231
He'll just send someone else.

30:19.984 --> 30:21.027
It's not fair.

30:23.988 --> 30:25.532
That's what the gun's for.

30:30.912 --> 30:31.788
All right.

30:33.331 --> 30:34.207
Oh.

30:35.291 --> 30:36.334
Almost forgot.

30:41.798 --> 30:43.174
Better watch your back.

30:44.050 --> 30:45.969
"Sleep tight, goose."

30:46.052 --> 30:47.679
"Sleep tight, moose."

30:47.762 --> 30:50.473
"Sleep tight,
bear with the fuzzy, fuzzy hair."

30:50.557 --> 30:53.977
[sighs] I meant to be here sooner.
There were a million documents to sign.

30:54.060 --> 30:57.939
-It's fine. We just got out of the bath.
-Oh, how's my little man?

30:58.022 --> 30:59.858
-He's still breathing.
-I know.

30:59.941 --> 31:01.025
-Ooh…
-[Dakota gurgling]

31:03.570 --> 31:05.280
When did you last change him?

31:05.363 --> 31:07.282
Oh. Just now.

31:07.365 --> 31:08.449
Mmm-mmm.

31:10.743 --> 31:12.662
Okay. Okay.

31:13.663 --> 31:15.748
-Okay.
-[Dakota crying]

31:15.832 --> 31:16.833
[gasps]

31:17.625 --> 31:18.710
What is that?

31:19.377 --> 31:21.254
His ding-a-lingy.

31:22.005 --> 31:23.965
It's a rash. Did you use the cream?

31:24.591 --> 31:25.550
Yeah, of course.

31:26.134 --> 31:27.260
Which one?

31:27.343 --> 31:29.512
The one that said diaper cream.

31:29.596 --> 31:32.557
There are two. I told you to use
the one in the side pocket.

31:32.640 --> 31:35.685
-Well, what's the difference?
-One works and one does not.

31:35.768 --> 31:39.063
-Then why do you have the other one?
-In case of emergency.

31:39.147 --> 31:40.523
That makes no sense.

31:40.607 --> 31:43.151
Well, now he's got a rug burn
on his crotch.

31:43.735 --> 31:46.571
-He didn't tell me that he was--
-Because he can't speak.

31:46.654 --> 31:49.490
No, I mean he didn't indicate
that he was uncomfortable.

31:49.574 --> 31:51.784
You know what,
just get me a new diaper, please.

31:52.785 --> 31:53.786
Okay.

31:55.246 --> 31:57.165
Yes. We're gonna get it fixed.

31:58.082 --> 31:59.167
I'm sorry. I…

31:59.751 --> 32:02.045
No, no. You know what? It's my fault.

32:02.962 --> 32:03.796
Why?

32:04.339 --> 32:07.050
Because I left a child with a child.

32:08.301 --> 32:10.303
[sighs] Okay. Almost.

32:14.182 --> 32:17.268
-All right, what do I owe you?
-Nothing.

32:19.103 --> 32:20.021
Fine.

32:25.443 --> 32:26.694
[sighs] Okay.

32:26.778 --> 32:27.779
I, um…

32:31.032 --> 32:34.243
really, really,
really wanted to get this one right.

32:36.955 --> 32:38.081
Why?

32:40.249 --> 32:42.794
I don't know.
I guess just to know I could.

32:44.212 --> 32:45.338
Sorry.

32:48.633 --> 32:50.176
Tell it to his little sac.

32:56.432 --> 32:57.433
[door closes]

33:10.530 --> 33:12.156
[door opens]

33:18.037 --> 33:19.038
Yeah.

33:22.333 --> 33:23.835
-[Rio grunts]
-Jesus!

33:24.669 --> 33:25.712
Rough day?

33:28.923 --> 33:30.425
Not what I planned.

33:34.053 --> 33:36.305
You got something you want to tell me?

33:50.778 --> 33:52.363
[suspenseful music playing]

33:55.992 --> 33:58.286
'Cause I'd really
love to hear it from you.

34:06.878 --> 34:08.921
Straight from the banker's mouth.

34:18.097 --> 34:19.682
[music stops]

34:22.268 --> 34:23.603
I'm sorry, what?

34:24.437 --> 34:25.688
Books didn't balance.

34:27.732 --> 34:29.108
Oh. Um…

34:33.529 --> 34:36.532
One of your customers
needed a little bit more persuading.

34:37.116 --> 34:38.868
That's this month and next.

34:40.828 --> 34:41.746
Good.

34:42.288 --> 34:44.082
Glad it didn't have to get messy.

34:44.832 --> 34:45.917
Glad it's done.

34:48.169 --> 34:49.337
[chuckling] What's that?

34:49.962 --> 34:52.965
Oh, darling, no, no.
We're just getting started.

34:55.301 --> 34:56.385
Why?

34:57.970 --> 34:59.889
'Cause I've got to sit tight.

35:01.349 --> 35:02.433
Why me?

35:04.227 --> 35:05.353
You're my girl.

35:08.648 --> 35:11.150
Unless… you're not.

35:12.985 --> 35:13.820
It just…

35:14.570 --> 35:17.198
you know, feels a little risky.

35:17.281 --> 35:18.241
How's that?

35:20.326 --> 35:23.704
Shaking down all these people
when maybe someone is still watching.

35:25.164 --> 35:27.875
Yeah, but all they'll see is you.

35:28.751 --> 35:29.669
So…

35:34.590 --> 35:36.300
[TV playing indistinctly]

35:48.896 --> 35:50.022
Whoa.

35:50.731 --> 35:52.984
-Hmm?
-You still going, huh?

35:54.944 --> 35:56.154
Is that a problem?

36:04.996 --> 36:07.123
Can you take Harry to quiz bowl tomorrow?

36:08.124 --> 36:09.083
Let me check.

36:20.511 --> 36:22.054
You like Mama's new purse?

36:25.516 --> 36:26.350
Yeah.

36:29.437 --> 36:30.813
You think I'm worth it?

36:32.690 --> 36:33.816
Of course you are.

36:35.735 --> 36:36.736
Who is she?

36:43.117 --> 36:43.951
Who are you?

36:46.078 --> 36:48.247
It's so obvious, I can't even believe it.

36:48.831 --> 36:50.583
You're going through my car now?

36:51.334 --> 36:53.461
-What's next, my email?
-Oh, I already did that.

36:53.544 --> 36:55.087
So you think I'm some kinda player?

36:55.171 --> 36:57.381
Exhausted all the time, coming home late--

36:57.465 --> 36:59.842
-He had me making a business deal.
-Body glitter?

36:59.926 --> 37:01.677
Listen, don't get me wrong, she would've--

37:01.761 --> 37:03.638
Smelling like all kinds of wrong.

37:03.721 --> 37:05.014
That's part of the job.

37:05.097 --> 37:07.350
What about the lying
straight to my damn face?

37:07.433 --> 37:11.062
-I am not sleeping around.
-Is that part of the job, too?

37:11.729 --> 37:14.815
-It is when you put me in this.
-What does that mean?

37:16.525 --> 37:18.444
Who you think's paying off your debt?

37:22.740 --> 37:24.867
You said insurance covered it.

37:24.951 --> 37:26.202
It's not about money.

37:26.827 --> 37:28.162
What's it about, then?

37:31.123 --> 37:32.124
[sighs]

37:34.252 --> 37:36.629
You can't just take from a guy like him.

37:39.924 --> 37:41.092
[sighs]

37:42.009 --> 37:43.010
Jesus.

37:43.886 --> 37:44.804
Yeah.

37:48.516 --> 37:49.934
What's he got you into?

37:50.726 --> 37:52.186
Whatever Gene needs.

37:53.271 --> 37:54.563
For how long?

37:55.356 --> 37:57.066
How long you into it with your guy?

38:02.405 --> 38:03.406
[sighs]

38:11.163 --> 38:12.415
No, keep it.

38:14.292 --> 38:15.668
It looks real, right?

38:17.837 --> 38:20.006
-Perfect? I mean, close.
-Mmm-hmm.

38:20.089 --> 38:22.466
There's 300 more coming right behind it.

38:39.483 --> 38:40.818
Are you okay?

38:41.485 --> 38:42.903
Yeah. Why?

38:44.363 --> 38:46.365
I just never knew you had a floor.

38:46.449 --> 38:48.617
-It's wood!
-Who knew?

38:49.452 --> 38:51.495
Oh, hey, by the way,
the kitch is fully stocked.

38:51.579 --> 38:54.582
You got your sour gummy candies,
your sweet gummy candies,

38:54.665 --> 38:57.126
and then a bunch
of the really sour sweet ones.

38:58.669 --> 39:00.671
Is this 'cause of the baby thing?

39:01.839 --> 39:03.341
What baby thing?

39:03.424 --> 39:05.426
What Nancy said about Dakota.

39:06.719 --> 39:07.762
What did she say?

39:08.888 --> 39:11.223
That he loved you
and you did really awesome.

39:12.933 --> 39:13.768
Cool.

39:18.898 --> 39:19.899
[sighs]

39:20.775 --> 39:22.526
-Mom?
-Yeah?

39:23.527 --> 39:25.780
Why'd you take the turtle out?

39:27.073 --> 39:28.115
I didn't.

39:29.867 --> 39:30.868
[sighs]

39:31.369 --> 39:33.913
-[man 1] On the outside.
-[door buzzes]

39:33.996 --> 39:37.416
-[man 2] Gate three.
-[man 3] Gate three.

39:37.500 --> 39:39.794
["The Beacon" playing]

39:40.795 --> 39:41.962
[door buzzes]

40:04.568 --> 40:09.115
<i>♪ I feel the gloom</i>
<i>On those peaceful days ♪</i>

40:12.535 --> 40:17.081
<i>♪ What overwhelms my existence ♪</i>

40:20.334 --> 40:24.922
<i>♪ I see the beacon and it's warning me ♪</i>

40:28.634 --> 40:31.429
<i>♪ To wander into your arms… ♪</i>

40:32.012 --> 40:33.139
How'd you do it?

40:41.856 --> 40:45.609
Look, I'm not some big,
dirty thug. I can't keep doing this.

40:45.693 --> 40:47.445
Don't have much of a choice.

40:48.112 --> 40:51.699
Well, can't we just… sit tight?

40:52.408 --> 40:56.078
Like I said, don't have much of a choice.

40:56.829 --> 40:57.997
Why?

40:59.415 --> 41:02.001
Because I also have people to answer to.

41:05.796 --> 41:06.922
Oh, and, uh…

41:07.548 --> 41:09.383
they're gonna wanna meet you.

41:09.467 --> 41:11.552
[song continues playing]

41:22.146 --> 41:23.522
He's got a boss.

41:29.153 --> 41:31.155
[closing theme music playing]
